'''Boron''' ({{FA|315}}-{{FA|408|n}}<ref name="WJBeor">{{WJ|14}}, ''(i) The House of Bëor''</ref>) was the third head of the [[House of Bëor]].

== History ==
Boron was the son of [[Baran]] and grandson of [[Bëor|Bëor the Old]], and inherited the title of family head after his father's death in {{FA|380|n}}. He had two sons, [[Boromir (Lord of Ladros)|Boromir]] and [[Belegor]], the eldest of which inherited his title and also became the first [[Lord of Ladros]].<ref name="WJBeor"/>

==Etymology==
''Boron'' is a word in [[Old Noldorin]] and [[Ilkorin]] for "Steadfast, trusty man, faithful vassal".<ref>{{LR|Etymologies}}, root BOR-</ref>

